    • Method Detail

      • allotAsMuchAsPossibleTo

        void allotAsMuchAsPossibleTo(FundsUseTracker fundsUseTracker)
        Allots as much money as possible from this source tracker to the given use tracker. The most that can be allotted is the smaller of the unallotted amount of the source tracker and the unallotted amount of the use tracker. If there is already an allotment between the source and the use, remove it and create a new one for the total alloted amount
        Parameters:
        fundsUseTracker - the fund use tracker to which funds will be allotted

      • allotUpTo

        void allotUpTo(FundsUseTracker fundsUseTracker,
             MonetaryAmount amountToAllot)
        Allots up to the amount given from this source tracker to the given use tracker. The most that can be allotted is the smallest of the unallotted amount of the source tracker, the unallotted amount of the use tracker and the given amount. If there is already an allotment between the source and the use, remove it and create a new one for the sum of the already allotted amount and the amountToAllot
        Parameters:
        fundsUseTracker - the fund use tracker to which funds will be allotted
        amountToAllot - the amount to try to allot between the source tracker and the use tracker
